Package: miCCI
Title: Quality-Preserving Charlson Comorbidity Index Estimation Under Diagnosis Anonymisation
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Gaetan", "Kamdje Wabo",
           email = "gaetan.kamdjewabo@medma.uni-heidelberg.de",
           role  = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Piotr",  "Sokolowski", role = "aut"),
    person("Fabian", "Siegel",     role = "aut"))
Description: Five computational strategies for reconstructing the
    Charlson Comorbidity Index (CCI) from truncated (anonymised)
    ICD-10-GM codes. S1 deterministic interval, S2 inclusion-exclusion
    expected value, S3 multiple imputation, S4 Bayesian Dirichlet
    posterior median, and a cross-validated Super Learner meta
    estimator (van der Laan, Polley & Hubbard 2007) that combines
    S1 to S4 via non-negative least squares. Reference population
    frequencies default to the German Federal Statistical Office
    table 23131-01 (Destatis), but any data.table of the same schema
    can be passed in. CCI mapping is the Quan et al. (2005) enhanced
    ICD-10 algorithm. The pipeline is split into a heavy compute stage
    and a fast reporting stage so that plots and tables can be
    regenerated without recomputing the estimates.
